Problem: Given an array of 0's and 1's, move all of the 0's to the beginning of the array and all of the 1's to the end of the array.
Solution:
```java
  public static int[] bringZeroForwardOneBackward(int[] arr){
   int count = 0;
    for (int i : arr){
      if(i == 0){
        count++;
      }
    }  

    Arrays.fill(arr,0,count,0);
    Arrays.fill(arr,count+1,arr.length-1,1);

    System.out.println( Arrays.toString(arr));
    System.out.println(arr.length);
    return arr;
    }
}
```

Question 2: What is the best data structure for a phone book with names and phone numbers? Code an example solution and explain.
Answer: A map would be ideal because it's a key value pair data structure.

```java
public static class phoneBook{
        private Map<Integer, String> map = new HashMap<>();
        private String name;
        private Integer ph;
        public void addPhoneNumber(Integer ph, String name){
            map.put(ph,name);
        }
        public Set getPhoneNumbers(){
            return map.keySet();
        }
        public Object[] getNames(){
            return map.values().toArray();
        }


    }
```

Question 3 : Remove duplicates in this list.


```java
    public static ArrayList<Integer> 
    removeDuplicateInAList(ArrayList<Integer> arr){
      int i =0;
      while(i<arr.size()){
        for(int j = 1; j < arr.size(); j++){
          if(arr.get(i) == arr.get(j)){
            arr.remove(j);
          }
        }
        i++;
      }
       return arr;
    }
```

PHP session timeout

```php
if (isset($_SESSION['LAST_ACTIVITY']) 
&& (time() - $_SESSION['LAST_ACTIVITY'] > 1800)) {
    // last request was more than 30 minutes ago
    session_unset(); // unset $_SESSION variable for the run-time 
    session_destroy(); // destroy session data in storage
}
$_SESSION['LAST_ACTIVITY'] = time();
```

